node.text:
The latest episode of @womanevolve podcast reminded me of a time I received a “report card” from my son. I was defensive before he could even speak to me. 

The need to defend is also the desire to protect our fragility and insecurity. The more you find peace with your humanity you leave room for God to grow you where you need it the most.

node.title: You’re not going to do everything well all of the time. You’re growing.

node.text:
Fatherhood has a different definition for everyone. Sometimes that definition is beautiful and filled with love. Sometimes it’s complicated and difficult to explain. Other times the definition is flat out painful. 

Today I’m grateful that my dad gave me an incredible, sacrificial, loving, generous, hilarious, loyal, and kind definition of fatherhood. I know for sure that he’s given me the very best that he has. Not only was your best good enough daddy, it was more than enough. 

I could spend the rest of my life living and sharing what you’ve poured into me and it will still never fully measure up to how much wisdom, strength, love, and character you’ve given me. 
My cup overflows. Happy Father’s Day  Daddy! I love you so much. 

May this prayer reach every heart who needs it the most.

node.title: My dad @bishopjakes is why I define fatherhood as covering.

The latest episode of @womanevolve podcast reminded me of a time I received a “report card” from my son. I was defensive before he could even speak to me. 

The need to defend is also the desire to protect our fragility and insecurity. The more you find peace with your humanity you leave room for God to grow you where you need it the most.

node.text:
I just want to see you be free. And not that fake free that makes you look successful on the outside while crumbling within. I want to create an environment where you can finally exhale then breathe divinity in. 

Divinity that clears your focus, drowns your fears, and stretches your belief. Divinity that convicts your sin and strengthens your will. 

When I pray for you. When God gives me the grace to serve you. I don’t just see you. I see the nations connected to you. I see the pure little girl still alive and waiting to be seen. I see hope. I see power. I see strength. Tag a woman who needs to see these words. 

___________

When I think about 11/5-6th I see you free. We’re having a virtual and in-person experience and today is the LAST day to get the early bird registration for this time of refreshing, freedom, and evolving. 

Visit womanevolve.com for all the details.

node.text:
I’m more like Eve than I realize… that one thought changed my life. It felt crazy at first. After all, I’d spent my entire life thinking of the ways I’d drag her when I got to heaven. 

I judged her even as a teen mom. I didn’t stop judging her when I was waitressing at the strip club by the college I’d dropped out of. Judgment stayed with me even during the series of toxic relationships that shattered my heart. I looked down on her even when standing in a divorce court. I so vividly saw her mistakes, failure, and sin, but never the pressure and deception that initiated her demise. 

I also missed how God didn’t throw her away, but rather helped her to rebuild. I should’ve seen it though because I was rebuilding my life from the garbage bin. The same faithful God that knew Eve would eat from that tree knew that I (and you) would too. 

If my life could only have one work this would be it. I’m praying I have the opportunity to continue learning and sharing all that God reveals to me, but for now I’m at peace knowing I’ve challenged a few women to experience Eve’s revolution for their own soul. 

Five months later and this book continues to invade the hearts of many. To God Be The Glory! 

#nowomanleftbehind #womanevolve #sarahjakesroberts

You made me want to feel. 

And not just a pinch to confirm that a moment is real, but  rather a commitment to remain open because your love didn’t come with fear. 

I thought the pain and the drama had turned pieces of my heart to stone, but you saw gold still peeking from my soul. 

And I know it’s not possible because superheroes aren’t real but I swear you’ve had me in the air for 7+ whole years. 

I guess that’s what happens when the supernatural embodies one person completely. To be loved by you is to see glimpses of heaven on earth. 

It’s your birthday, but I’m the one whose been rebirthed. You make it all make sense. With you the sum is always joy. 

When I get to heaven I’m going to give your angels a great big tip for protecting and guiding your every step. 

Happy Birthday to my warrior, king of a husband. Loving you is my favorite thing to do. ❤️

node.text:
I don’t know who needs to hear this, but buy you some clothes that fit and stop beating yourself up for gaining weight. 

Obviously this has been one of the most stressful seasons the world has seen, but let’s get into those moments when it felt like life dragged you around like a rag doll with personal struggles that’ll never make headlines. 

Your body has shown up for you in ways you could have never planned for. You survived loss, transition, growth, promotion, failure, disease, and success. 

You can’t beat yourself up and take care of yourself at the same time. Put on your stretchy pants. Be gentle with yourself and love yourself from the inside out. 

Also, if you’re trying to gain some pounds after stress caused you to lose weight please DM me so that  I can donate my extra to your ministry.

“The moments we have been offended by someone else are always crystal clear. Yet the moments we have been the cause of an offense for another remain quite blurry.” - 

In other words @ryanleak told me I’m more comfortable being the victim than owning the moments when I’ve been a villain! 🥴

One of the reasons I love the Woman Evolve Bookclub is that the books don’t just help you strengthen where you’re already strong, but rather build you in the areas that are underdeveloped. 

If you’re looking to end the last quarter of 2021 with likeminded women on a journey of development, reflection, and connection you should consider plugging in to the bookclub. 

I’ve been hand picking books that range from poetry, fiction, spirituality, and mental health. Plotting the track of development for the women in this group has been one of my favorite things to do this year. 

The bi-monthly live discussions, study guides, playlist, and private FB group have made me realize I’m not the only one having ups and downs, but still committing to growth. 

If you want to plug in and get connected to the bookclub go to womanevolvebookclub.com for all the details.
